revision.text:
'''Abortion in Greece''' has been fully legalized since 1986, when law 1609/1986 was passed effective from 3 July 1986.<ref>[https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/pdf/10.1016/S0968-8080(04)24001-0 Use of Contraception and Abortion in Greece: A Review, Elizabeth Ioannidi-Kapolou, p.174]</ref><ref name=abo>[http://www.bioethics.org.gr/Embryokriari.pdf RIGHTS OF EMBRYO AND  FOETUS IN PUBLIC AND  PRIVATE  LAW, Ismini Kriari-Catranis et al., p. 9]</ref>. [[Abortion]]s can be performed on-demand in hospitals for women whose pregnancies have not exceeded twelve weeks.<ref name="data">[http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/6235557.stm#greece Europe's abortion rules]</ref> In the case of [[rape]] or [[incest]], an abortion can occur as late as nineteen weeks, and as late as twenty-four weeks in the case of fetal abnormalities.<ref name="data" /> In case of inevitable risk to the life of the pregnant woman or a risk of serious and continuous damage to her physical or mental health, termination of pregnancy is legal any time before birth<ref name=abo/><ref>[http://www.0-18.gr/downloads/ethniki-ekthesi-dsdp COMMITTEE ON THE RIGHTS OF THE CHILD CONSIDERATION OF REPORTS SUBMITTED BY STATES PARTIES UNDER ARTICLE 44 OF THE CONVENTION, p. 9]</ref>. Girls under the age of 18 must get written permission from a parent or guardian before being allowed an abortion.<ref name="data" />

{{as of|2007}}, the abortion rate was 7.2 abortions per 1000 women aged 15-44 years.<ref name="un2013">{{Cite web | title = World Abortion Policies 2013 | publisher = United Nations | year = 2013 | url = https://www.un.org/en/development/desa/population/publications/policy/world-abortion-policies-2013.shtml | accessdate = 3 March 2014 }}</ref>

