'''''Ajaloo ilu''''' (''History of Beauty'') is a 1991 novel by [[Estonia]]n author [[Viivi Luik]], re-issued in 2002 and revised in 2011. It has been translated into Finnish, Danish, Dutch, Russian, Swedish, Norwegian, German, Latvian, Icelandic, Hungarian, French, Catalan, English and Albanian.

The plot unfolds in [[Latvia]] and [[Estonia]] in August 1968, when [[Soviet troops]] occupied [[Czechoslovakia]] during the [[Prague Spring]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arhiiv.err.ee/vaata/viivi-luik-ja-tema-romaan-quot-ajaloo-ilu-quot/similar-179017|title=Viivi Luik ja tema romaan "Ajaloo ilu".|publisher=Arhiiv.err.ee|accessdate=1 April 2015|language=Estonian}}</ref> The leading character is a 21-year-old woman who falls in love with a sculptor.

