{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2017}} {{Infobox public transit | box_width = | name = BG Voz | image = File:BG Voz logo.jpg | alt = | imagesize = 250px | caption = Train logo | native_name = {{lang-sr|БГ Воз}} | owner = | area served = [[Belgrade]] | locale = | transit_type = | lines = | line_number = 2 | start = | end = | stations = 17 | daily_ridership = | annual_ridership = | chief_executive = <!-- or | key_people = --> | headquarters = | website = | began_operation = {{start date and age|2010}} | operation_will_start = | ended_operation = | operator = [[GSP Belgrade]] | marks = | host = | character = | vehicles = | train_length = | headway = | system_length = <!-- {{convert|0|mi|km|abbr=on}} --> | notrack = | track_gauge = <!-- {{Track gauge|sg|allk=on}} --> | ogauge = <!-- {{Track gauge|sg|allk=on}} --> | minimum_radius_of_curvature = <!-- {{convert|0|ft|0|in|mm|0}} --> | el = | average_speed = <!-- {{convert|0|mph|km/h|abbr=on}} --> | top_speed = <!-- {{convert|0|mph|km/h|abbr=on}} --> | map = | map_name = | map_state = <!-- show or collapsed --> }} '''BG Voz''' (stylized as '''BG:Voz'''; {{lang-sr-cyr|БГ Вoз}}) is an urban rail system that serves the city of [[Belgrade]], Serbia. It is operated by the public transit corporation [[GSP Belgrade]] and is a part of the integrated [[BusPlus]] system.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.expatserbia.com/once-youre-here/public-transport/413-bg-voz |title=Archived copy |access-date=August 24, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130905111325/http://www.expatserbia.com/once-youre-here/public-transport/413-bg-voz |archive-date=September 5, 2013 |dead-url=yes |df=mdy-all }}</ref>
==Lines in service== ===Line 1=== {{BG Voz Line 1}} BG:Voz began service between [[New Belgrade]] and [[Pančevo Bridge]] stations on September 1, 2010. Starting from April 15, 2011, the line has been extended westward to [[Batajnica]]. Further extension across the Danube, towards Krnjača and Ovča in 2016, was financed from the [[RZD International]] credit. The total travel time between the first and the last stop is 50 minutes. At peak times, trains run every 15 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.zeleznicesrbije.com/active/sr-latin/home/glavna_navigacija/bg_voz_novi_gradski_prevoz.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=August 24, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130717110734/http://www.zeleznicesrbije.com/active/sr-latin/home/glavna_navigacija/bg_voz_novi_gradski_prevoz.html |archive-date=July 17, 2013 |dead-url=yes |df=mdy-all }}</ref> That line currently contains 13 stations (corresponding to Srbija voz Line 55<ref>[http://www.srbvoz.rs/kurir2017.pdf Srbija voz schedule for 2017], pp 92–95 {{Sr icon}} (accessed February 24, 2017)</ref> and Belgrade public transport Line 100<ref>[http://bgprevoz.rs/linije/100 BG prevoz line 100]</ref>): *{{rws|Batajnica}} *{{rws|Zemun Polje}} *{{rws|Zemun}} *{{rws|Tošin Bunar}} *[[Novi Beograd railway station|New Belgrade]] *[[Prokop railway station|Belgrade center]] *[[Karađorđe's Park railway station|Karađorđev Park]] *{{rws|Vukov Spomenik}} *Pančevo Bridge *[[Krnjača Most railway station|Krnjača–most]] *{{rws|Krnjača}} *{{rws|Sebeš}} *{{rws|Ovča}}
<ref>http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/naslovna/ekonomija/aktuelno.239.html:533600-Pruga-temelj-prevoza-u-gradu</ref><ref>http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/beograd.74.html:535899-Beograd-Vozom-do-Resnika-i-Ovce</ref> <ref>http://www.beograd.rs/cir/beoinfo/1737149-sinisa-mali-master-plan-saobracajne-infrastrukture-osnova-za-razvoj-beograda/</ref>
===Line 2=== {{BG Voz Line 2}} The second line, between [[Prokop railway station|Belgrade Center]] and [[Resnik railway station|Resnik]], began revenue operations on April 13, 2018. Service frequency is one train every hour.<ref>[http://infrazs.rs/2018/04/bg-vozovi-izmedju-resnika-i-beograd-centra-redovni/ БГ возови између Ресника и Београд Центра редовни]</ref> It is expected that, beginning in mid-2018, some trains from the first line would be re-directed to line 2 (due to announced Belgrade-Budapest railroad reconstruction). Additionally, this line would be extended towards Ovča in order to partially compensate for the reductions in service on the first line. However, due to the nature of [[Belgrade railway junction]], it would temporarily bypass the Belgrade Center station.<ref>[https://www.busevi.com/glas-putnika/pitanje-prijava-predlog-informacija/od-13-04-2018-pocinje-sa-radom-druga-linija-bgvoz-a-na-relaciji-resnik-zel-st-beograd-centar/?show_answer=30330 Od 13.04.2018. počinje sa radom druga linija BG:voz-a na relaciji “Resnik – Žel.St. /Beograd centar/” ]</ref> The line currently has only 5 stations: *{{rws|Resnik}} *{{rws|Kijevo}} *{{rws|Kneževac}} *{{rws|Rakovica}} *[[Prokop railway station|Belgrade center]]
==References== {{reflist}}
