{{Infobox mountain | name = Chilchalphorn | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 3040 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 192 | prominence_ref= <ref>[[Swisstopo]] map</ref> | parent_peak = [[Fanellhorn]] | location = [[Graubünden]], [[Switzerland]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | range = [[Lepontine Alps]] | range_coordinates = | coordinates = {{coord|46|31|59.3|N|9|9|15|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
The '''Chilchalphorn''' is a [[mountain]] of the [[Lepontine Alps]], overlooking [[Hinterrhein, Switzerland|Hinterrhein]] in the canton of [[Graubünden]]. On the northern side of the mountain lies a glacier named ''Fanellgletscher''.
