[[File:Collins_Reef_building_by_Vietnam.jpg|thumb|300px|Vietnamese structure on Collins Reef]]
[[File:Union Banks en.svg|thumb|300px|alt=Map of the Union Banks|Map of the [[Union Banks]] ]]

'''Collins Reef''' (also known as '''Johnson North Reef'''/Johnson Reef North, {{lang-vi|Đá Cô Lin}}, {{zh|c=鬼喊礁|p=Guǐhǎn jiāo}}, {{lang-tl|Roxas}}) is a [[Vietnam]]ese occupied and controlled reef and the westernmost feature of [[Union Banks]] [[Atoll]] near the centre of [[Dangerous Ground (South China Sea)|Dangerous Ground]] in the [[Spratly islands]] in the [[South China Sea]].<ref>{{cite book |title=China Sea Pilot - Volume II - NP 31 |date=2012 |publisher=United Kingdom Hydrographic Office |location= Taunton |url= http://mdnautical.com/sailing-directions-pilots/15739-np-31-china-sea-pilot-vol-ii-10th-2012-edition-9780707742762.html}}</ref> It is also claimed by China and Taiwan. 

== Location ==
Collins Reef lies at {{coord|9.772738|114.256230|display=it|format=dms}} ({{coord|9.772738|114.256230}}), to the northwest of [[Johnson South Reef]], at the southwestern corner of the Union Banks.<ref>{{cite news |last=Diola |first=Camille |title=IN PHOTOS: China's reclamation on Mabini Reef |url= http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2014/05/15/1323405/photos-chinas-reclamation-mabini-reef |accessdate= 19 May 2014 |newspaper= Philippine Star |date= 15 May 2014 }}</ref>

