The '''imperial election of 1138''' was an [[imperial election]] held to select the [[Holy Roman Emperor|emperor]] of the [[Holy Roman Empire]].  It took place in [[Koblenz]] on March 7.

[[Conrad III of Germany]] was named [[Holy Roman Emperor]] as a result of the election.

