The '''Pomerania euroregion''' or '''EUROREGION POMERANIA''' was set up in 1995 as one of the [[euroregion]]s, thought to connect regions divided between states of the [[European Union]]. The name is taken from the region of [[Pomerania]], yet the euroregion is of a different shape than the historical region. It comprises German [[Western Pomerania]] and [[Uckermark]], Polish [[Zachodniopomorskie]], and [[Scania]] in [[Sweden]].
==See also== *[[List of euroregions]]
