{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Bunia |latin = Dioecesis Buniaensis |country = {{flag|Democratic Republic of Congo}} |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kisangani|Kisangani]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 22,470 |population = 710,226 |population_as_of = 2006 |catholics = 439,700 |catholics_percent= 61.9 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Dieudonné Uringi Uuci]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Bunia''' ({{lang-la|Buniaën(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Bunia]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kisangani|Kisangani]] in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
==History== * June 27, 1922: Established as Apostolic Prefecture of Lake Albert from the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Stanley Falls]] and the [[Apostolic Vicariate of Uganda]] in [[Uganda]] * December 11, 1933: Promoted as Apostolic Vicariate of Lake Albert * November 10, 1959: Promoted as Diocese of Bunia
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Bunia ([[Latin Rite]]) ** Bishop Dieudonné Uringi Uuci (since 2005.04.01) ** Bishop [[Léonard Dhejju]] (1984.07.02 – 2002.04.06) ** Bishop [[Gabriel Ukec]] (1964.09.29 – 1984.07.02) ** Bishop [[Alphonse Joseph Matthijsen]], [[M. Afr.]] (1959.11.10 – 1963.08.19) * Vicars Apostolic of Lake Albert (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Alphonse Joseph Matthijsen, M. Afr. (1933.12.11 – 1959.11.10) * Prefects Apostolic of Lake Albert (Latin Rite) ** Bishop Alphonse Joseph Matthijsen, M. Afr. (1922.06.21 – 1933.12.11)
