'''Socialist Revolution Party of Benin''' ({{lang-fr|Parti de la Révolution Socialiste du Bénin}}) was a [[Marxism-Leninism|Marxist-Leninist]] [[political party]] operating in [[Togo]] and [[Dahomey]]. It was founded in [[Cotonou]] on July 28, 1959.<ref name="b">{{cite book|title=L'Afrique et l'Asie|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lgMsAQAAIAAJ|edition=45-48|year=1959|page=66}}</ref><ref name="a">{{cite book|title=Le Contrat social|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5BIiAQAAMAAJ|volume=6|year=1962|publisher=Institut d'histoire sociale.|page=19}}</ref><ref>[https://www.jstor.org/stable/2610375]</ref> The party united [[Juvento]] dissidents from Togo and Dahomeyan trade unionists.<ref name="b"/> The founding declaration of the party was signed by Max Mensah Aithson (Togo) and Théophile Béhanzin (Dahomey).<ref name="a"/>

