'''Taein Heo clan''' ({{Korean|태인 허씨|泰仁 許氏}}) was one of the [[Korean clans]]. Their [[Bon-gwan]] was in [[Jeongeup]], [[North Jeolla Province]]. According to the research in 2015, the number of Taein Heo clan was 11990. Their founder was {{ill|Heo Sa mun|ja|許士文}}. {{ill|Heo Sa mun|ja|許士文}} was a 30th descendant of [[Heo Hwang-ok]] who was a queen of [[Satavahana dynasty]] and an empress of [[Suro of Geumgwan Gaya]], a first king of [[Gaya confederacy]]. {{ill|Heo Sa mun|ja|許士文}} was a loyalist of [[Taejo of Goryeo]] in [[Goryeo dynasty]] and was appointed as Prince of Sisan ({{hanja|詩山君}}).<ref>{{Cite book|author=|date=|title=Doosan Encyclopedia 허 許|publisher=[[Doosan Encyclopedia]]|url=http://terms.naver.com/entry.nhn?docId=1162549&cid=40942&categoryId=31639&mobile}}</ref>
