{{Expand Italian|Comunicazioni a San Marino|date=March 2012}}
[[File:Cabina telefonica San Marino.JPG|thumb|Phone booth in the [[City of San Marino]]]]
This article provides an outline of the [[telecommunications]] infrastructure in [[San Marino]].

== Telephone ==
{{Unreferenced section|date=April 2011}}
There are no [[telephone company|telephone providers]] in San Marino as the [[Italy|Italian]] system provides services. In 2002 there were 20,600 [[landlines]] in use, as well as 16,800 [[mobile phones]].

== Television and radio ==
San Marino has only one [[television network]], [[San Marino RTV (TV channel)|San Marino RTV]], which is owned by a company [[San Marino RTV|with the same name]].<ref>{{Citeweb|url=http://www.sanmarinortv.sm/default.asp?id=7|title=San Marino RTV-Television (Italian)|accessdate=}}</ref> In 1997, there were approximately 9,000 television sets in the country.

San Marino has two [[radio networks]], [[Radio San Marino]] and [[Radio San Marino Classic]], also owned by San Marino RTV.<ref>{{Citeweb|url=http://www.sanmarinortv.sm/radio/default.asp?id=16|title=San Marino RTV-Radio (Italian)|accessdate=}}</ref> In 1997, there were approximately 16,000 radios in San Marino.

== Internet ==
{{Expand section|date=April 2011}}
In 2010 there were 17,000 [[Internet]] users in San Marino.<ref>{{Citeweb|url=http://www.internetworldstats.com/euro/sm.htm|title=European Internet Usage-San Marino|accessdate=}}</ref> San Marino's [[internet domain]] is [[.sm]].

