{{BadenWürttemberg-struct-stub}}

The '''Visegrad Patent Institute''' ('''VPI''') is an intergovernmental organization for cooperation in the field of [[patent]]s, created by the national [[patent office]]s of the four [[Visegrad countries]], namely the [[Czech Republic]], [[Hungary]], [[Poland]] and [[Slovakia]].<ref name=PCT>{{cite web|url=http://www.wipo.int/edocs/pctndocs/en/2015/pct_news_2015_10.pdf|title=Assembly of the PCT Union|date=October 14, 2015|work=PCT Newsletter 10/2015|publisher=WIPO|accessdate=20 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visegradgroup.eu/calendar/2015/the-visegrad-group-v4|title=The Visegrad Group (V4) Countries Establish a Joint Patent Institute|year=2015|publisher=Visegrád Group|accessdate=19 October 2015}}</ref> The Agreement on the Visegrad Patent Institute (VPI Agreement) was signed in [[Bratislava]] on February 26, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wipo.int/edocs/mdocs/govbody/en/pct_a_47/pct_a_47_6_add.pdf|title=APPOINTMENT OF THE VISEGRAD PATENT INSTITUTE AS AN INTERNATIONAL SEARCHING AND PRELIMINARY EXAMINING AUTHORITY UNDER THE PCT – UPDATE ON RECENT DEVELOPMENTS|date=September 15, 2015|publisher=WIPO|accessdate=19 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://bbj.hu/economy/visegrad-countries-sign-agreement-on-joint-patent-institute_93326|title=Visegrad countries sign agreement on joint patent institute|date=February 27, 2015|work=[[Budapest Business Journal]]|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/b21af338-fd64-11e4-9e96-00144feabdc0.html#axzz3pnUQ9K3h|title=Central and eastern Europe innovators hungry for action|last=Foy|first=Henry|date=June 5, 2015|work=The Financial Times|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref> The Institute aims at operating as an [[International Searching Authority]] (ISA) and [[International Preliminary Examining Authorities]] (IPEA) under the [[Patent Cooperation Treaty]] (PCT) as from July 1, 2016.<ref name=PCT/>
According to Slovak Foreign Affairs Minister [[Miroslav Lajčák]], the signature of the agreement on creating the Visegrad Patent Institute is an important milestone in the history of the [[Visegrad Four]], the alliance between Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland and Slovakia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://spectator.sme.sk/c/20058482/lajcak-weight-of-v4-grows-in-eyes-of-foreign-partners.html|title=Lajčák: Weight of V4 grows in eyes of foreign partners|date=June 30, 2015|work=[[The Slovak Spectator]]|accessdate=27 October 2015}}</ref>
